<i>to everyone except them.</i>

13:48.250 --> 13:51.166
I went behind Jordan's back
and got my junk rewired.

13:52.542 --> 13:56.125
She was sweet to me.
Sweet, bobbo.

13:56.875 --> 13:58.750
What the hell
do you make of that?

14:01.500 --> 14:04.375
Carla thinks she's so tough.
You know, she's been around the block.

14:04.458 --> 14:06.625
She's from the block.
Enough about the block!

14:06.709 --> 14:09.500
It's not my fault
my family had an orchard.

14:09.583 --> 14:12.667
For 4 years I've had to listen to Elliot
complain about her problems.

14:12.750 --> 14:15.583
"My parents are too rich."
"I slept with J.D. again."

14:15.667 --> 14:17.250
"Why can't I gain any weight?"

14:17.333 --> 14:19.500
Well, I got problems of my own.
I'm from the block.

14:19.583 --> 14:21.959
I wanted to help her.
I just wish she could've heard me.

14:22.041 --> 14:23.583
Ok, Jerry, you're out.

14:23.667 --> 14:24.875
-Laverne?
-Mm-hmm?

14:24.959 --> 14:25.792
Can I talk to you?

14:25.875 --> 14:28.625
Perry, believe me
when I say I'm proud to welcome you

14:28.709 --> 14:31.750
to what I like to call
the seedless grapes club. But still...

14:31.834 --> 14:36.208
I have just one obvious, and hopefully
chop-busting question...

14:36.291 --> 14:38.542
Why the hell are you talking
to me about this?

14:40.709 --> 14:42.625
(all)
I guess I should be talking to her.

14:47.208 --> 14:49.834
Jordan, Jordan, why aren't
you more upset about this?

14:49.917 --> 14:51.417
Honest to God, I don't get it.

14:51.500 --> 14:54.000
I mean, normally you'd go to your mother's
for a bitch refresher course

14:54.083 --> 14:56.917
and then you'd come right back here,
just swinging for the fences.

14:57.000 --> 14:58.959
You know what?
I'd love to stay and chat,

14:59.041 --> 15:01.667
but if we're late for ballet, Jack won't
get a spot by the bathroom

15:01.750 --> 15:02.875
and then he'll pee in his tights.

15:02.959 --> 15:07.125
I'm sorry, my son is taking ballet?

15:07.709 --> 15:09.709
Come on, Jordan, he's already got
an overbearing mother

15:09.792 --> 15:11.417
and a fairly prominent lisp.

15:11.500 --> 15:14.208
If we stick him in the tights, we might as
well just go ahead

15:14.291 --> 15:16.250
and get him a time share
on fire island.

15:16.333 --> 15:18.834
Oh, I haven't even decided
if I'm gonna make him gay yet.

15:18.917 --> 15:21.166
Oh, I see what this is.

15:21.250 --> 15:23.583
This is the payback, huh?

15:23.667 --> 15:25.750
Perry, I didn't freak out
because you and I

15:25.834 --> 15:27.583
are 2 very independent people
in a relationship

15:27.667 --> 15:29.834
and we don't always
share our feelings.

15:29.917 --> 15:32.709
I didn't get angry
because I'm not surprised.

15:32.792 --> 15:34.500
Let's go ballet.

15:37.041 --> 15:40.041
Do I wish it were different?
Sometimes.

15:40.125 --> 15:42.834
But whatever you and I
have is working,

15:42.917 --> 15:45.208
so I guess I just
have to live with it.

15:45.291 --> 15:46.458
Bye, daddy.

15:51.542 --> 15:54.917
-So how you feeling down there?
-Oh, great. Great.

15:55.000 --> 15:56.125
Reverse it.

16:02.125 --> 16:03.417
See ya, lads.

16:06.458 --> 16:08.000
Oh, man.

16:08.083 --> 16:10.458
I know we feel guilty,
ok, but it's over.

16:10.542 --> 16:12.458
It's not like there's gonna
be any ramifications.

16:14.458 --> 16:18.542
You have one day to come up
with another gorgeous Irishman.

16:18.625 --> 16:21.000
-One day.
-What?

16:21.083 --> 16:24.083
The Todd appreciates hot,
regardless of gender.

16:30.750 --> 16:33.125
I'm glad Billy's gone.
He was such a jerk.

16:33.208 --> 16:34.750
He kept calling me Bonnie.

16:34.834 --> 16:36.125
Bonnie means pretty.

16:37.250 --> 16:40.208
Oh, my God,
I will never love like that again.

16:41.333 --> 16:44.458
You know I wasn't really mad about
Billy or the whole flaking thing.

16:44.542 --> 16:46.709
I remember hugging you
the day of my wedding

16:46.792 --> 16:49.667
and thinking to myself, even though
the other 2 bridesmaids were my sisters,

16:49.750 --> 16:51.750
I felt closer to you.

16:52.625 --> 16:55.291
When did we stop
being best friends?

16:55.375 --> 16:57.333
It feels like it took us so long
to get to that point

16:57.417 --> 16:59.542
and then it's gone away
so quickly, you know?

16:59.625 --> 17:01.125
Well, it's my fault.

17:01.208 --> 17:03.417
I've been burying myself
in being married.

17:03.500 --> 17:04.959
Oh, please, it is your first year.

17:05.041 --> 17:07.959
I should've been the one
to make the extra effort.

17:08.041 --> 17:09.375
So, what now?

17:10.542 --> 17:12.667
-We try harder.
-All right.

17:13.875 --> 17:15.583
Yo, who taught you
how to fight like that?

17:16.291 --> 17:18.667
When you grow up on an Orchard,
you don't have much choice.

17:20.500 --> 17:22.750
-Apple thieves.
-Ah.

17:30.291 --> 17:31.500
What the hell happened to you?

17:31.583 --> 17:34.083
I got them to reverse
the vasectomy.

17:34.166 --> 17:37.000
What an incredibly
normal thing to do.

17:37.083 --> 17:39.125
Jordan, let me talk for a second.

17:39.208 --> 17:43.542
I've been trained for many years
to take any emotion I feel,

17:43.625 --> 17:47.458
push it down, and then let it out
by drinking way too much

17:47.542 --> 17:50.208
and by yelling at the football players
on my TV screen.

17:50.291 --> 17:53.125
And I really thought
I hit the jackpot

17:53.208 --> 17:57.542
when I finally met a woman who was
as disturbed and closed off as I am.

17:57.625 --> 17:58.792
Thank you.

17:58.875 --> 18:03.208
You're welcome.
Still, now I want more. I really do.

18:03.291 --> 18:05.750
I want to talk about things.
Not everything. Not everything.

18:05.834 --> 18:07.709
I definitely don't want
to talk about everything.

18:07.792 --> 18:10.417
For instance, I don't need to know
when you beat up a woman in the park

18:10.500 --> 18:15.333
because her purse is the same color
as yours, but things that matter.

18:15.417 --> 18:18.458
Things that are important
to us as a family.

18:18.542 --> 18:22.583
And I know that there are guys
who bring flowers

18:22.667 --> 18:24.667
and there are guys
who write love songs.

18:26.166 --> 18:27.750
But, Jordan, I'm a guy
sitting in front of you here

18:27.834 --> 18:29.333
with a twice-operated-on penis

18:29.417 --> 18:33.291
that says I want to be a couple
that communicates more openly.

18:33.375 --> 18:36.041
What kind of guy writes love songs?

18:36.125 --> 18:38.625
Guys whose mothers make
them go to ballet class.

18:38.709 --> 18:40.125
Fair enough.

18:42.542 --> 18:44.041
You know how much
I love you.

18:44.125 --> 18:45.458
I love you too.

18:49.417 --> 18:52.083
Ok, now that we're being
all open and honest...

18:52.166 --> 18:54.458
-Yeah.
-I do not want to have any more kids.

18:54.542 --> 18:57.959
-I think you should get the vasectomy.
-Fantastic.

19:05.875 --> 19:08.875
-I warned you!
-What the hell happened?

19:08.959 --> 19:11.125
He woke up and said something snarky,
so I popped him again.

19:11.208 --> 19:13.083
Are you serious?!

19:13.166 --> 19:14.875
-Boo!
-Ah!

19:16.583 --> 19:17.417
Nah.

19:17.500 --> 19:19.542
Oh, you think
scaring people's funny?

19:19.625 --> 19:21.083
Well, good, 'cause you're dying.

19:21.166 --> 19:22.625
John Dorian, you are a doctor.

19:22.709 --> 19:23.667
Well, he started it.

19:23.750 --> 19:25.000
Sorry about your face, man.

19:25.083 --> 19:27.250
Oh, please, I threw the first punch.
It was my fault.

19:27.333 --> 19:29.583
Right, then, I'm off.

19:30.625 --> 19:32.250
Supposed to be
in Florence by midnight.

19:32.333 --> 19:33.542
How the hell are you
gonna do that?

19:34.458 --> 19:37.250
Her apartment's 2 blocks away.
Should be no problem at all.

19:37.834 --> 19:40.667
Hey, we're sorry about the whole
incarceration thing.

19:40.750 --> 19:43.083
No worries.
Life's too short to hold a grudge.

19:43.166 --> 19:45.542
But still, you 2 boys
might want to ask yourselves

19:45.625 --> 19:46.709
why you contacted the authorities

19:46.792 --> 19:48.917
and didn't have the decency
to come and talk to me first.

19:49.000 --> 19:52.291
But I shall let you two partners
figure that out.

19:52.375 --> 19:54.166
By the way,
you're a gorgeous couple.

19:54.250 --> 19:55.417
Good luck to you.

19:56.333 --> 19:57.750
See you, lads!

20:01.083 --> 20:03.333
When I was alive,
I wish I had lived one day

20:03.417 --> 20:05.208
like he lives every day of his life.

20:05.291 --> 20:07.834
Dead people don't talk, Jerry.

20:07.917 --> 20:09.458
(J.D.)
<i>We weren't really mad at Jerry.</i>

20:09.542 --> 20:11.625
<i>What we realized was</i>
<i>that we were jealous of Billy</i>

20:11.709 --> 20:14.667
<i>because he was out living life</i>
<i>and Turk and I weren't.</i>

20:14.750 --> 20:18.000
<i>I guess it's important</i>
<i>not to take life for granted.</i>

20:18.083 --> 20:19.667
<i>Whether it's appreciating</i>
<i>your relationships...</i>

20:19.750 --> 20:22.125
All righty, let's go for
the hat trick there, doc.

20:22.208 --> 20:25.083
-Are you sure?
-Hey, doc, zip it, grip it, and snip it!

20:27.250 --> 20:28.709
(both laughing)

20:28.792 --> 20:30.375
(J.D.)
<i>Or renewing your friendships.</i>

20:31.709 --> 20:32.834
-(snorts)
-I almost peed.

20:32.917 --> 20:34.458
(coughing and laughing)

20:34.542 --> 20:36.250
(J.D.) <i>For Turk and I,</i>
<i>it was important to just get out</i>

20:36.333 --> 20:38.667
